                            <comment id="17898080" author="mjsax" created="Thu, 14 Nov 2024 00:34:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for filing this ticket. &#8211; Can you share your Json `Deserializer` code? What I don&apos;t understand right now is, how a checked exception could be thrown? The interface does not declare any exceptions, and thus only `RuntimeException` should be allowed: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java#L61&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java#L61&lt;/a&gt; &#8211; So I would assume that any checked exception must be caught inside `deserialize(...)` and would be re-thrown as unchecked exception?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17898209" author="JIRAUSER307706" created="Thu, 14 Nov 2024 09:34:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mjsax&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mjsax&quot;&gt;mjsax&lt;/a&gt; . We use Kotlin and it doesnt have checked exceptions at compile time, so even deserializer like this would compile:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// kotlin
&lt;/span&gt;Deserializer { topic: &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;, bytes: ByteArray -&amp;gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; IOException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;error&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
} &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And the error in runtime would be exactly that without wrapping:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Exception in thread &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;main&quot;&lt;/span&gt; java.io.IOException: error
...stack... &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suppose, its the same problem for Scala. And its also technically possible in Java, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/a/37748872&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://stackoverflow.com/a/37748872&lt;/a&gt;. Or Lombok SneakyThrows &lt;a href=&quot;https://projectlombok.org/features/SneakyThrows&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://projectlombok.org/features/SneakyThrows&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17898369" author="mjsax" created="Thu, 14 Nov 2024 18:13:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah. Thanks for clarification. That&apos;s helpful.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree that we should fix this... As it&apos;s a regression, I&apos;ll mark is as blocker for 3.9.1 and 4.0.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Current work-around for 3.9.0 would be adding `try-catch` and re-throw as `RuntimeException`.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17898610" author="chia7712" created="Fri, 15 Nov 2024 12:48:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;trunk: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/f02c28b21dc4d89e1d7f2e16f8f9e067a9575e61&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/f02c28b21dc4d89e1d7f2e16f8f9e067a9575e61&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

